<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[421,1818,576,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">
A blackish, ordinary sized ant, known from Nicobar, 
<collectingCountry box="[1552,1706,1166,1208]" name="Réunion" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Reunion</collectingCountry>
, Cargados and Chagas Islands, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1130,1216,1259]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">India</collectingCountry>
. 
<materialsCitation country="Guam" location="Fullaway" pageId="7" pageNumber="182" specimenCount="1">
Collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1405,1511,1216,1259]" name="Guam" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Guam</collectingCountry>
by 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0E4F7F497E635A28B4F7FDC41367734A:833998847E635A28B36EFB4410B272BF" box="[1596,1765,1216,1259]" country="Guam" name="Fullaway" pageId="7" pageNumber="182">Fullaway</location>
in 1911
</materialsCitation>
. We found it one of the common ants in 1936.
</paragraph>
